...giving a kiss,
embracing someone...


533
00:30:58.440 --> 00:31:00.730
...or telling a tasteless joke.

534
00:31:00.940 --> 00:31:05.450
That side lies in wait,
pushing back the other side...


535
00:31:05.610 --> 00:31:08.950
...which is more beautiful,
purer and deeper.


536
00:31:09.490 --> 00:31:13.910
The truth is that no one knows
Anne's better side...


537
00:31:14.080 --> 00:31:16.040
...and that's why most people...

538
00:31:16.210 --> 00:31:17.500
...can't stand me.

539
00:31:17.670 --> 00:31:21.840
I can be an amusing clown
for an afternoon...


540
00:31:22.000 --> 00:31:25.130
...but then everyone
has had enough of me.


541
00:31:25.800 --> 00:31:29.510
So the nice Anne has never once...

542
00:31:29.680 --> 00:31:32.470
...been seen in company.

543
00:31:32.640 --> 00:31:35.980
But, in her loneliness,
she always triumphs.


544
00:31:36.390 --> 00:31:39.020
My best to you. Anne Frank.
Anne's diary ends here."


545
00:31:39.190 --> 00:31:40.770
It ends here. Why?

546
00:31:40.980 --> 00:31:44.650
Because the police turned up
at the rooms...


547
00:31:44.820 --> 00:31:47.610
...where they were hiding
and deported them.


548
00:31:47.780 --> 00:31:49.490
She died shortly after.

549
00:31:49.660 --> 00:31:53.030
That's what I asked earlier.
We talked about it.


550
00:31:53.200 --> 00:31:55.790
I learn about Anne Frank...

551
00:31:56.000 --> 00:31:59.670
...because she talks about herself
and so I get to know her.


552
00:32:00.210 --> 00:32:04.380
When I ask you to write
your own self-portraits...


553
00:32:04.670 --> 00:32:06.340
...I'll expect the same.

554
00:32:06.510 --> 00:32:10.390
In other words, to learn things
through your feelings.


555
00:32:10.550 --> 00:32:12.680
You can talk about facts...

556
00:32:13.560 --> 00:32:17.770
...that will allow me
to know you better.


557
00:32:19.230 --> 00:32:20.270
Yes, Lucie?

558
00:32:20.440 --> 00:32:25.320
What we write
won't be as gripping as...


559
00:32:25.530 --> 00:32:27.820
...as what Anne Frank wrote.

560
00:32:29.860 --> 00:32:31.820
Our lives aren't as gripping.

561
00:32:32.030 --> 00:32:33.410
All right.

562
00:32:33.580 --> 00:32:35.830
Juliette?

563
00:32:36.040 --> 00:32:39.830
Someone aged 70
could talk about their life...


564
00:32:40.040 --> 00:32:43.420
...but we have nothing to tell at 13.

565
00:32:44.550 --> 00:32:48.460
At 14, 15 or even 13,
you've had experiences.


566
00:32:48.920 --> 00:32:53.340
Less than someone aged 70.
They've lived a lot more.


567
00:32:53.760 --> 00:32:55.810
- Okay.
- They've seen life.


568
00:32:55.970 --> 00:32:59.890
It's funny. You don't think
your lives are interesting.


569
00:33:00.060 --> 00:33:03.770
We just come to school, go home,
eat and sleep.


570
00:33:04.570 --> 00:33:07.440
You come to school, eat, sleep.
Fine.


571
00:33:07.610 --> 00:33:10.400
The bare facts of your life are dull.

572
00:33:10.570 --> 00:33:14.570
- But what you feel is interesting.
- That's my business.


573
00:33:14.740 --> 00:33:17.200
Maybe, but I'm interested.

574
00:33:17.370 --> 00:33:19.080
That's different.

575
00:33:19.250 --> 00:33:20.660
Why is it different?

576
00:33:21.960 --> 00:33:24.000
Because you're a teacher.

577
00:33:24.790 --> 00:33:26.540
It's not the teacher talking.

578
00:33:26.710 --> 00:33:29.090
- It's your job.
- It's the human being.


579
00:33:31.590 --> 00:33:35.390
I think you're only saying that
to get us to talk and stuff...


580
00:33:35.600 --> 00:33:36.850
...but it's not true.

581
00:33:38.180 --> 00:33:39.520
It isn't?

582
00:33:39.680 --> 00:33:40.810
What isn't true?

583
00:33:40.980 --> 00:33:44.480
The fact that you're interested
in knowing all that.


584
00:33:44.650 --> 00:33:46.650
So I'm not interested at all...

585
00:33:46.820 --> 00:33:49.150
...and I'm pushing at this...

586
00:33:49.320 --> 00:33:51.570
...to convince you it's interesting?

587
00:33:51.740 --> 00:33:54.280
Not as much as you say.

588
00:33:54.950 --> 00:33:57.490
Maybe I am exaggerating a little.

589
00:33:58.790 --> 00:34:02.040
It's only natural
since you don't agree with me.


590
00:34:02.210 --> 00:34:04.670
But, deep down, 
I'm totally sincere.

591
00:34:04.830 --> 00:34:08.630
Why is it such a problem for you...

592
00:34:08.800 --> 00:34:10.130
...to talk about your lives?

593
00:34:10.300 --> 00:34:11.340
Boubacar?

594
00:34:11.510 --> 00:34:13.510
Well, there's stuff...

595
00:34:14.840 --> 00:34:16.470
There's private stuff.

596
00:34:16.850 --> 00:34:18.850
Of course.

597
00:34:19.310 --> 00:34:23.020
What could be hard to say
about your private lives?


598
00:34:23.810 --> 00:34:25.190
Burak?

599
00:34:25.350 --> 00:34:28.440
We may be ashamed
to say certain things.


600
00:34:28.820 --> 00:34:31.780
Yes, it has to do with shame.

601
00:34:31.940 --> 00:34:35.450
Things you find it hard to say
and even harder to write.


602
00:34:37.530 --> 00:34:40.030
In your life,
when were you ashamed?


603
00:34:40.200 --> 00:34:43.370
You can be ashamed of a pal's mom.

604
00:34:43.540 --> 00:34:46.870
Why? Because you find her ugly?

605
00:34:48.880 --> 00:34:51.590
No. For instance, Rabah's mom.

606
00:34:51.760 --> 00:34:54.010
She offered me lunch but I refused...

607
00:34:54.170 --> 00:34:56.090
...because I was ashamed.

608
00:34:56.260 --> 00:34:57.760
Ashamed to eat with her?

609
00:34:58.390 --> 00:35:00.680
Because it's beneath you?

610
00:35:01.350 --> 00:35:03.850
I don't understand. Tell me why.

611
00:35:05.060 --> 00:35:08.020
I'm ashamed to eat with her
because I respect her.


612
00:35:08.190 --> 00:35:11.480
You never eat
with people you respect?


613
00:35:11.690 --> 00:35:14.570
I mean, she's not my girlfriend.

614
00:35:15.860 --> 00:35:19.740
You can only eat
with a girlfriend?


615
00:35:19.910 --> 00:35:22.370
Tell me why. I'm interested.

616
00:35:22.540 --> 00:35:26.750
I can't explain it.
In any case, I'm ashamed.


617
00:35:26.920 --> 00:35:29.330
I always hang out with Rabah...

618
00:35:29.500 --> 00:35:31.920
...so I respect his mom.

619
00:35:32.090 --> 00:35:33.710
I don't eat in front of her.

620
00:35:34.210 --> 00:35:38.340
So if Boubacar eats in front of us,
he doesn't respect us.


621
00:35:38.890 --> 00:35:40.600
No, it's not that.

622
00:35:42.220 --> 00:35:44.100
You can't understand.

623
00:35:44.270 --> 00:35:45.930
I'm not smart enough?

624
00:35:46.100 --> 00:35:48.270
You just can't understand.

625
00:35:48.850 --> 00:35:52.610
- Rabah?
- I was at a party with Camemberters.


626
00:35:52.770 --> 00:35:54.400
"Camemberters?"

627
00:35:54.570 --> 00:35:55.690
Yeah, like you.

628
00:35:55.860 --> 00:35:56.990
What's a Camemberter?

629
00:35:57.150 --> 00:35:59.610
Someone who stinks of cheese.

630
00:35:59.780 --> 00:36:02.950
So the people at the party
stank of cheese?


631
00:36:04.240 --> 00:36:06.580
They were all in suits and ties.

632
00:36:06.750 --> 00:36:09.790
I was in my baggies
and got these weird looks.


633
00:36:09.960 --> 00:36:11.580
- You were ashamed?
- Yeah.


634
00:36:11.750 --> 00:36:13.290
Because of the looks.

635
00:36:13.460 --> 00:36:16.010
They were embarrassed
because of you...


636
00:36:16.170 --> 00:36:17.970
...and you felt the same.

637
00:36:18.130 --> 00:36:19.590
They weren't embarrassed.

638
00:36:19.760 --> 00:36:22.890
They looked at me
like I was an E.T.

639
00:36:23.310 --> 00:36:24.390
You are an E.T.

640
00:36:24.560 --> 00:36:26.310
"Why's that Arab here?"

641
00:36:26.480 --> 00:36:28.350
Okay, so it was a race thing.

642
00:36:28.520 --> 00:36:29.890
I don't know.

643
00:36:31.480 --> 00:36:33.610
But the snacks
were bacon-flavored.


644
00:36:34.900 --> 00:36:36.070
So?

645
00:36:36.820 --> 00:36:39.320
So I abstained.

646
00:36:39.490 --> 00:36:42.950
Right. Bacon, ham. Okay, I get it.

647
00:36:43.620 --> 00:36:44.780
Wei?

648
00:36:44.950 --> 00:36:48.000
Young people now have no shame.

649
00:36:48.160 --> 00:36:50.290
Young people now? Like you?

650
00:36:51.790 --> 00:36:52.960
Drop your briefs.

651
00:36:53.130 --> 00:36:54.630
They have no shame.

652
00:36:55.420 --> 00:36:57.710
It's normal. Always normal.

653
00:36:58.300 --> 00:37:00.550
- Are you like them?
- No, I'm not.


654
00:37:00.720 --> 00:37:01.840
Are you ashamed?

655
00:37:02.010 --> 00:37:03.970
Yes, ashamed for them.

656
00:37:07.140 --> 00:37:09.480
I'll waste your ugly mug.

657
00:37:10.690 --> 00:37:14.020
Anyone can speak
but you stay polite, okay.


658
00:37:14.820 --> 00:37:17.440
So why are you ashamed for them?

659
00:37:17.610 --> 00:37:19.150
They have no shame.

660
00:37:19.320 --> 00:37:22.110
They yell, they hit each other.

661
00:37:22.320 --> 00:37:25.660
They make jokes, bother others.
No shame.


662
00:37:26.200 --> 00:37:27.950
Wei, aren't you confusing...

663
00:37:28.120 --> 00:37:29.660
...shame and discipline?

664
00:37:29.830 --> 00:37:32.210
You find the others...

665
00:37:32.370 --> 00:37:34.080
...rowdy and impolite?

666
00:37:35.670 --> 00:37:38.420
- It can be shameful too.
- Louise?


667
00:37:38.590 --> 00:37:41.220
You can be ashamed
of your appearance.


668
00:37:41.380 --> 00:37:43.180
Absolutely.

669
00:37:44.340 --> 00:37:45.970
Tell me, Louise...

670
00:37:46.680 --> 00:37:48.720
...what are you ashamed of?

671
00:37:52.350 --> 00:37:53.770
My ears.

672
00:37:53.940 --> 00:37:55.310
Your ears?

673
00:37:55.480 --> 00:37:56.560
Can we see?

674
00:37:56.730 --> 00:37:58.650
You're ashamed of your ears?

675
00:37:58.860 --> 00:38:01.400
What's wrong with them?

676
00:38:01.860 --> 00:38:03.360
They stick out.

677
00:38:03.530 --> 00:38:05.950
- You think they stick out.
- Mine too.


678
00:38:06.120 --> 00:38:08.080
I think that covers it all.

679
00:38:08.240 --> 00:38:11.700
You have all you need
to figure it out.


680
00:38:11.870 --> 00:38:14.580
Take out your exercise books.

681
00:38:16.040 --> 00:38:20.630
Note the following exercise
for next Thursday.


682
00:38:23.880 --> 00:38:28.390
It's very simple:
"Write your self-portrait."


683
00:38:34.100 --> 00:38:36.600
A self-portrait isn't
an autobiography.


684
00:38:36.770 --> 00:38:39.440
I don't want your life story.

685
00:38:40.280 --> 00:38:42.530
Describe yourself
and your personality.


686
00:38:44.740 --> 00:38:47.910
We'll read them in class
and see how we can use them.


687
00:38:49.910 --> 00:38:50.990
Don't forget.

688
00:39:00.340 --> 00:39:01.800
Khoumba.

689
00:39:02.420 --> 00:39:04.260
You know I want to see you.

690
00:39:10.220 --> 00:39:12.100
Give me your report book.

691
00:39:12.270 --> 00:39:13.310
Why?

692
00:39:13.480 --> 00:39:15.310
You know why.

693
00:39:21.320 --> 00:39:25.490
No, give it to me. Politely.
That's enough now.


694
00:39:26.780 --> 00:39:29.120
Put your photo on it.

695
00:39:35.000 --> 00:39:38.670
Is it normal to refuse to read
when a teacher asks you to?


696
00:39:38.830 --> 00:39:41.840
- Is that normal?
- There's others in the class.


697
00:39:42.250 --> 00:39:44.630
I can't turn a blind eye to this.

698
00:39:44.800 --> 00:39:45.970
Can I?

699
00:39:50.600 --> 00:39:52.600
What happened this summer?

700
00:39:54.640 --> 00:39:56.810
What happened during the vacation?

701
00:39:57.020 --> 00:39:58.690
- I didn't see you.
- I know.


702
00:39:58.850 --> 00:40:02.110
I'm intrigued.
At the end of the year in June...


703
00:40:02.270 --> 00:40:04.730
...we'd gotten on pretty well together.

704
00:40:04.900 --> 00:40:07.570
You participated in class.
Since September...


705
00:40:07.740 --> 00:40:09.990
...since the start of this year...

706
00:40:10.490 --> 00:40:12.200
...you're not cooperative...

707
00:40:13.120 --> 00:40:14.370
...you keep sulking...

708
00:40:14.540 --> 00:40:16.870
...you refuse to read.
What happened?


709
00:40:17.040 --> 00:40:20.210
I don't like reading now.
Can you hurry, please?


710
00:40:20.630 --> 00:40:22.210
No, I won't hurry.

711
00:40:29.220 --> 00:40:33.300
Explain. Why have things changed
all of a sudden?


712
00:40:34.010 --> 00:40:36.060
I can't stay a kid forever.

713
00:40:37.060 --> 00:40:39.560
So it's a kid thing to cooperate?

714
00:40:39.730 --> 00:40:41.190
That's it.

715
00:40:41.350 --> 00:40:42.980
There's others in the class.

716
00:40:43.150 --> 00:40:45.230
Of course, when you work, it's...

717
00:40:47.070 --> 00:40:48.530
I haven't finished.

718
00:40:48.700 --> 00:40:50.400
My mom's waiting for me.

719
00:40:50.570 --> 00:40:52.530
I want an apology first.

720
00:40:53.030 --> 00:40:55.240
An apology for what you did.

721
00:40:56.540 --> 00:40:58.580
"I apologize for being insolent, sir."

722
00:40:58.750 --> 00:41:00.040
Sorry. Okay?

723
00:41:00.210 --> 00:41:02.210
No, not "sorry."

724
00:41:02.380 --> 00:41:04.420
"I apologize for being insolent."

725
00:41:04.710 --> 00:41:05.840
Go ahead.

726
00:41:07.920 --> 00:41:09.380
I apologize, sir...

727
00:41:09.550 --> 00:41:12.430
No, "I apologize for being insolent."

728
00:41:12.590 --> 00:41:15.220
Be sincere. I want a real apology.

729
00:41:15.390 --> 00:41:17.350
Can you hurry up, please?

730
00:41:17.560 --> 00:41:19.810
- My mom's waiting--
- For your apology.


731
00:41:19.980 --> 00:41:21.350
Let's deal with this.

732
00:41:21.560 --> 00:41:23.440
I want a sincere apology...

733
00:41:23.610 --> 00:41:26.570
...that'll stand
for the rest of the year.


734
00:41:26.900 --> 00:41:28.780
We won't go on like this.

735
00:41:29.400 --> 00:41:32.450
I apologize for being insolent.

736
00:41:33.870 --> 00:41:34.950
More conviction.

737
00:41:36.080 --> 00:41:39.450
- I'm not saying it 50 times.
- You two.


738
00:41:39.620 --> 00:41:40.750
What are you up to?

739
00:41:40.910 --> 00:41:42.040
We're waiting.

740
00:41:42.210 --> 00:41:43.250
May I?

741
00:41:43.420 --> 00:41:45.130
Hurry, I'm listening.

742
00:41:45.790 --> 00:41:49.630
I apologize for being insolent.
May I go now, please?


743
00:41:56.930 --> 00:41:57.970
Cut it out.

744
00:41:58.140 --> 00:41:59.970
I didn't mean it.

745
00:42:10.860 --> 00:42:15.450
Two weeks ago, at the last meeting...

746
00:42:15.620 --> 00:42:17.320
...the teachers suggested...

747
00:42:18.330 --> 00:42:22.160
...introducing a penalty-point system
for the students...


748
00:42:22.330 --> 00:42:25.120
...based on the driving-license
system.


749
00:42:25.830 --> 00:42:28.460
If students broke a rule...

750
00:42:28.960 --> 00:42:31.130
...they would lose points.

751
00:42:31.300 --> 00:42:34.510
As it's the teachers' idea,
I'll let them speak.


752
00:42:34.680 --> 00:42:36.640
Since last September...

753
00:42:36.800 --> 00:42:41.930
...we've noticed an increase
in problems within the school.


754
00:42:42.520 --> 00:42:45.440
Punishment has no effect
on the students.


755
00:42:45.650 --> 00:42:46.980
So we had the idea...

756
00:42:47.150 --> 00:42:48.690
...of a penalty system.

757
00:42:48.860 --> 00:42:53.360
The students would have,
for example, six points each...


758
00:42:53.530 --> 00:42:57.870
...and, depending on the misdeed,
they'd lose one or two points.


759
00:42:58.030 --> 00:43:00.450
And when they run out of points?

760
00:43:00.660 --> 00:43:03.660
They go before
the disciplinary committee.


761
00:43:04.000 --> 00:43:06.330
As a parents' representative...

762
00:43:06.500 --> 00:43:10.840
...this is typical
of the school's bad habits.


763
00:43:11.550 --> 00:43:14.720
You always condemn the students...

764
00:43:15.180 --> 00:43:16.720
...but never praise them.

765
00:43:16.890 --> 00:43:18.890
They earn praise on their own.

766
00:43:19.050 --> 00:43:23.060
They do it with their grades,
by moving up a class...


767
00:43:23.220 --> 00:43:25.730
...and we do it in staff meetings...

768
00:43:25.890 --> 00:43:28.440
...by encouraging them to work.

769
00:43:28.610 --> 00:43:32.780
There's the honor roll,
the congratulations...


770
00:43:32.940 --> 00:43:34.530
That all counts.

771
00:43:34.690 --> 00:43:36.360
In your system...

772
00:43:36.530 --> 00:43:39.070
...you take away points
for misdeeds...


773
00:43:39.410 --> 00:43:40.910
...but why not go further...

774
00:43:41.080 --> 00:43:44.240
...and give points to those
who do good things?


775
00:43:44.410 --> 00:43:46.040
Like gold stars.

776
00:43:46.580 --> 00:43:49.250
I'm all for praising the students...

777
00:43:49.420 --> 00:43:53.630
...but if students collect points
and end up with 34 points, say...


778
00:43:54.840 --> 00:43:57.630
...that leaves room
for all kinds of trouble...


779
00:43:57.800 --> 00:43:59.050
...we can't control.

780
00:43:59.220 --> 00:44:03.260
Without going as far
as these imaginary 34 points...


781
00:44:03.430 --> 00:44:06.680
...six points to start with...

782
00:44:06.850 --> 00:44:10.150
...means they can cause trouble
without punishment.


783
00:44:10.310 --> 00:44:14.530
Losing a point or two
isn't a real punishment.


784
00:44:14.940 --> 00:44:18.240
It can create
a dangerous sense of impunity.


785
00:44:18.410 --> 00:44:21.620
For me, the idea's
totally wrongheaded.


786
00:44:22.240 --> 00:44:23.370
In that case...

787
00:44:23.540 --> 00:44:26.080
...we could find a punishment...

788
00:44:26.250 --> 00:44:30.620
...where the students
lose all their points in one go.


789
00:44:31.250 --> 00:44:34.800
But why bother with the points
in that case?


790
00:44:35.760 --> 00:44:37.590
It's tricky.

791
00:44:37.970 --> 00:44:42.050
What you call a sense of impunity
gives us room to maneuver.


792
