01:43:47.140 --> 01:43:48.640
That's kind of logical.

1805
01:43:49.390 --> 01:43:51.470
Let's talk about that.

1806
01:43:52.600 --> 01:43:54.980
How many hearings last year?

1807
01:43:58.310 --> 01:43:59.980
Twelve at least.

1808
01:44:00.690 --> 01:44:01.820
Not that many.

1809
01:44:02.320 --> 01:44:03.610
He could be right.

1810
01:44:03.780 --> 01:44:07.280
I know, I'm on the committee
so I saw them all.


1811
01:44:07.450 --> 01:44:10.660
An average of two a month,
twelve in all...


1812
01:44:10.830 --> 01:44:12.490
...with an expulsion each time.

1813
01:44:12.660 --> 01:44:15.870
The hearing
is where we talk things over.


1814
01:44:16.040 --> 01:44:19.000
Okay, 12 students were expelled...

1815
01:44:19.170 --> 01:44:21.840
...but maybe
there was no other solution.


1816
01:44:22.210 --> 01:44:25.510
Twelve out of 12.

1817
01:44:25.680 --> 01:44:28.340
Talk about a debate.

1818
01:44:28.720 --> 01:44:31.470
But twelve out of 12 just means...

1819
01:44:31.640 --> 01:44:35.810
...when a student has a hearing,
it's too late.


1820
01:44:35.980 --> 01:44:37.350
Or it was justified.

1821
01:44:37.520 --> 01:44:40.690
Okay, things happen
that lead to a hearing.


1822
01:44:40.860 --> 01:44:42.570
But then what happens?

1823
01:44:43.230 --> 01:44:45.530
What do we expect from a hearing?

1824
01:44:45.700 --> 01:44:47.240
There are prior stages.

1825
01:44:47.450 --> 01:44:50.320
Pre-disciplinary committees.

1826
01:44:50.490 --> 01:44:53.740
We inform the parents,
the students are warned.


1827
01:44:54.750 --> 01:44:56.250
Not in this case.

1828
01:44:56.460 --> 01:44:58.040
We've no time.

1829
01:44:58.210 --> 01:44:59.710
It's pretty rare.

1830
01:45:00.460 --> 01:45:04.420
It's rare because we have
this final punishment...


1831
01:45:04.590 --> 01:45:07.470
...that allows us
to ignore the prior steps.


1832
01:45:07.760 --> 01:45:10.340
And even if we did use them...

1833
01:45:11.050 --> 01:45:14.470
...the simple fact
of expelling a student...


1834
01:45:14.770 --> 01:45:19.100
...is a disavowal
of everything we have tried.


1835
01:45:19.270 --> 01:45:23.110
Okay, but it's Souleymane's chance
to justify himself.


1836
01:45:23.270 --> 01:45:27.280
At a hearing, you don't speak.
You're scared.


1837
01:45:27.490 --> 01:45:30.360
- You're paralyzed.
- Exactly.


1838
01:45:30.620 --> 01:45:32.490
Let me sum this up.

1839
01:45:32.780 --> 01:45:35.290
He'll get a disciplinary hearing...

1840
01:45:35.500 --> 01:45:36.620
...he'll be expelled...

1841
01:45:36.790 --> 01:45:39.000
...and maybe even sent back to Mali.

1842
01:45:39.540 --> 01:45:41.630
You're being overdramatic.

1843
01:45:41.920 --> 01:45:43.540
No, I'm not.

1844
01:45:43.710 --> 01:45:47.300
Students who know him better
than any of us here...


1845
01:45:47.510 --> 01:45:50.590
...who know his father,
say that he is likely...


1846
01:45:50.760 --> 01:45:53.550
...to send him back to Mali after this.

1847
01:45:55.140 --> 01:45:57.600
Some are threatened
with boarding school...


1848
01:45:57.770 --> 01:46:01.020
...but it never happens.

1849
01:46:01.650 --> 01:46:03.270
It can happen.

1850
01:46:03.730 --> 01:46:07.480
A lot of parents spend their time
threatening their kids...


1851
01:46:07.650 --> 01:46:09.400
...with that.

1852
01:46:09.570 --> 01:46:11.610
You can't take it into account.

1853
01:46:12.320 --> 01:46:14.990
Even if there was just a slight risk...

1854
01:46:15.160 --> 01:46:17.450
...that a hearing could lead...

1855
01:46:17.620 --> 01:46:21.420
...to him being sent back,
I don't think I can take that risk.


1856
01:46:23.960 --> 01:46:27.130
It's like when you hesitate...

1857
01:46:27.300 --> 01:46:31.470
...over punishing a kid
because when he goes home...


1858
01:46:31.630 --> 01:46:33.840
...once that door closes...

1859
01:46:34.050 --> 01:46:37.850
...he'll get a beating from his parents.
We've all seen that.


1860
01:46:38.060 --> 01:46:42.770
But we still have to punish them
when they go too far.


1861
01:46:42.940 --> 01:46:46.770
Whatever the consequences,
which don't concern you.


1862
01:46:46.940 --> 01:46:51.190
So I ignore that? I know punishment
can have such a consequence...


1863
01:46:51.360 --> 01:46:54.780
...but I turn a
blind eye, is that it?

1864
01:46:54.950 --> 01:46:58.450
You can't take it into account
in every case.


1865
01:46:58.620 --> 01:47:01.370
The violence, him being sent back.

1866
01:47:01.580 --> 01:47:04.790
True, you have to consider it
but after a while...


1867
01:47:05.080 --> 01:47:07.460
No more Christmas presents.

1868
01:47:09.590 --> 01:47:11.470
It's a question of principle.

1869
01:47:11.630 --> 01:47:13.630
We each have a role to play.

1870
01:47:13.800 --> 01:47:17.100
We can't substitute ourselves
for the parents.


1871
01:47:18.720 --> 01:47:20.890
Sorry, but if I rewind the movie...

1872
01:47:21.100 --> 01:47:24.560
...it's a weird chain of events.
It starts with reprimands...


1873
01:47:24.730 --> 01:47:28.360
...when Souleymane forgets his things,
talks back.


1874
01:47:28.520 --> 01:47:30.900
We punish him. 
Again and again...

1875
01:47:31.110 --> 01:47:34.530
...until a disciplinary hearing
leading to who knows what.


1876
01:47:34.700 --> 01:47:38.240
Everything gets out of hand.

1877
01:47:38.410 --> 01:47:40.580
Sure, looking at it that way...

1878
01:47:40.750 --> 01:47:43.330
...it's really shocking.

1879
01:47:43.500 --> 01:47:47.830
But the school
won't be expelling Souleymane.


1880
01:47:48.250 --> 01:47:50.630
He's been gone for a while.

1881
01:48:28.580 --> 01:48:29.790
François.

1882
01:48:30.170 --> 01:48:32.670
I didn't expect you so soon.

1883
01:48:32.960 --> 01:48:35.590
Have you reached a decision?

1884
01:48:36.590 --> 01:48:39.050
I don't think I have much choice.

1885
01:48:45.270 --> 01:48:50.270
By the way, Julie told me
you had a heated exchange...


1886
01:48:50.440 --> 01:48:52.320
...with two girls in your class.

1887
01:48:52.900 --> 01:48:56.490
Yes, the two class reps
but it happened first so...


1888
01:48:56.700 --> 01:48:59.570
You apparently called them skanks.

1889
01:48:59.950 --> 01:49:01.490
Let's say that, yes.

1890
01:49:01.990 --> 01:49:04.160
That complicates things...

1891
01:49:04.330 --> 01:49:06.000
...but the problem remains.

1892
01:49:06.330 --> 01:49:09.170
I'd like you to mention it
in your report.


1893
01:49:09.330 --> 01:49:13.710
I don't want it used against us
at the disciplinary hearing.


1894
01:49:13.960 --> 01:49:17.260
Don't bother hiding it,
just write it down.


1895
01:49:17.430 --> 01:49:18.510
I understand.

1896
01:49:20.850 --> 01:49:23.180
I'll let you reread this...

1897
01:49:23.350 --> 01:49:25.720
...before we launch the procedure.

1898
01:49:26.310 --> 01:49:27.350
So I...

1899
01:49:27.520 --> 01:49:29.230
I just need to add...

1900
01:49:29.600 --> 01:49:31.860
Yes, without going into detail.

1901
01:49:33.360 --> 01:49:34.520
Does that suit you?

1902
01:50:05.260 --> 01:50:07.520
Can you take the minutes?

1903
01:50:26.290 --> 01:50:27.490
Please sit down.

1904
01:51:03.570 --> 01:51:05.450
"Carl tried to reason with him.

1905
01:51:05.620 --> 01:51:07.280
Souleymane broke free...

1906
01:51:07.450 --> 01:51:10.750
...swinging his bag that hit Khoumba
in the face.


1907
01:51:10.910 --> 01:51:14.080
He left, insulting everyone
and slamming the door.


1908
01:51:14.330 --> 01:51:17.460
I didn't go after him because
I needed to help Khoumba...


1909
01:51:17.630 --> 01:51:20.460
...whose eyebrow was bleeding."

1910
01:51:21.420 --> 01:51:25.090
Those are the facts
that led to today's hearing.


1911
01:51:25.390 --> 01:51:29.260
Madame, it doesn't mean
Souleymane is a bad boy.


1912
01:51:29.430 --> 01:51:31.730
That's not what we're saying.

1913
01:51:31.890 --> 01:51:34.560
But, sometimes,
a student in a class...


1914
01:51:34.730 --> 01:51:38.570
...through voluntary
or involuntary behavior...


1915
01:51:38.730 --> 01:51:43.450
...can create an atmosphere that
prevents the class from working.


1916
01:51:58.460 --> 01:52:01.460
Do you understand
what we're saying?


1917
01:52:03.170 --> 01:52:05.760
If I may say something, it's true...

1918
01:52:05.930 --> 01:52:10.180
...there had been a number of signs
that should have warned us.


1919
01:52:10.390 --> 01:52:12.430
We could have reacted sooner.

1920
01:52:13.890 --> 01:52:18.190
But now we have to deal
with an incident...


1921
01:52:18.400 --> 01:52:22.150
...that is fairly violent
and that's simply unacceptable.


1922
01:52:22.320 --> 01:52:26.400
I'd like to know
if you realize that, Souleymane?


1923
01:52:30.200 --> 01:52:33.870
We're not saying
you're deliberately violent.


1924
01:52:34.040 --> 01:52:38.920
The problem is you can't control
what you say and what you do.


1925
01:52:41.170 --> 01:52:43.510
Souleymane, we'd like to hear you.

1926
01:52:43.670 --> 01:52:47.180
You're here to express
your point of view. Go ahead.


1927
01:52:47.930 --> 01:52:51.010
I don't give a damn.
I've got nothing to say.


1928
01:52:51.220 --> 01:52:53.430
Do whatever you want to do.

1929
01:53:03.570 --> 01:53:04.690
Excuse me.

1930
01:53:09.820 --> 01:53:11.240
Monsieur, madame.

1931
01:53:15.160 --> 01:53:16.450
Can you translate?

1932
01:53:17.830 --> 01:53:19.710
She says I'm a good boy.

1933
01:53:22.750 --> 01:53:23.960
I do my homework.

1934
01:53:30.510 --> 01:53:35.180
I help my brothers and sisters
with their work when I can.


1935
01:53:40.480 --> 01:53:45.230
I always wash the dishes
and help her when I can.


1936
01:53:47.780 --> 01:53:51.780
We don't doubt he's a good son.
That's not the problem.


1937
01:53:51.990 --> 01:53:54.120
Let's consider his school record.

1938
01:53:54.290 --> 01:53:58.500
Excuse me, but could we focus
on the facts here?


1939
01:53:58.910 --> 01:54:01.540
Firstly, I'd like to say...

1940
01:54:01.790 --> 01:54:06.300
...that we're surprised to see the
teacher involved in the incident...


1941
01:54:06.510 --> 01:54:08.050
...on this committee.

1942
01:54:08.550 --> 01:54:10.220
We find it highly irregular.

1943
01:54:10.630 --> 01:54:15.260
It's true. It's odd
to be both judge and litigant.


1944
01:54:15.430 --> 01:54:20.940
First of all, Mr. Marin was elected
to the administrative board...


1945
01:54:21.100 --> 01:54:23.440
...as the teachers' representative.

1946
01:54:23.610 --> 01:54:24.650
Moreover...

1947
01:54:24.820 --> 01:54:30.150
...I think that the incident
that occurred in Mr. Marin's class...


1948
01:54:30.320 --> 01:54:33.070
...doesn't involve
the teacher directly.


1949
01:54:33.240 --> 01:54:35.330
I'm sorry...

1950
01:54:35.530 --> 01:54:39.910
...you mention some harsh words
spoken by the teacher.


1951
01:54:40.080 --> 01:54:42.790
Apparently,
you used the word "skanks"...


1952
01:54:42.960 --> 01:54:45.750
...to describe the class reps.
And that's a problem.


1953
01:54:45.920 --> 01:54:47.300
I did say that...

1954
01:54:47.460 --> 01:54:50.670
...but it wasn't something
that concerned Souleymane.


1955
01:54:50.840 --> 01:54:55.970
I think he used the excuse
of a rather heated exchange...


1956
01:54:56.140 --> 01:55:00.480
...to express the bad mood
that he was in that day.


1957
01:55:00.640 --> 01:55:02.270
He tried to defend them.

1958
01:55:02.440 --> 01:55:04.440
So I feel that it's relevant.

1959
01:55:04.610 --> 01:55:08.440
Sorry, but absolutely nothing
justifies...


1960
01:55:08.610 --> 01:55:10.860
...being disrespectful to a teacher...

1961
01:55:11.070 --> 01:55:15.490
...insulting everyone and leaving
a class without permission.


1962
01:55:17.660 --> 01:55:20.580
Souleymane,
do you have anything to say?


1963
01:55:21.830 --> 01:55:24.370
I don't know. What can I say?

1964
01:55:26.130 --> 01:55:27.590
Monsieur, madame.

1965
01:55:38.390 --> 01:55:39.560
What did she say?

1966
01:55:39.720 --> 01:55:41.890
The same thing again.

1967
01:55:55.320 --> 01:55:57.620
She apologizes on my behalf.

1968
01:57:03.270 --> 01:57:05.180
You can come back in now.

1969
01:57:28.790 --> 01:57:31.250
Madame, the committee
has conferred...


1970
01:57:31.420 --> 01:57:33.340
...and has decided
to expel Souleymane...


1971
01:57:33.500 --> 01:57:35.460
...from the school for good.

1972
01:57:35.630 --> 01:57:39.130
You will receive the ruling
by registered mail...


1973
01:57:39.300 --> 01:57:41.800
...and have eight days to appeal.

1974
01:57:49.270 --> 01:57:54.020
We shall do our best
to find Souleymane another school.


1975
01:57:57.820 --> 01:57:59.740
Goodbye, messieurs, dames.

1976
01:58:03.370 --> 01:58:08.250
Souleymane, come to see me
before the end of the week, please.


1977
01:58:40.900 --> 01:58:42.570
Mathematical proportionality.

1978
01:58:44.070 --> 01:58:47.700
This year, you learned
mathematical proportionality.


1979
01:58:47.870 --> 01:58:49.080
All right.

1980
01:58:49.330 --> 01:58:50.870
I liked science.

1981
01:58:51.040 --> 01:58:53.420
What you learned,
not what you liked.


1982
01:58:53.580 --> 01:58:55.790
If you liked it, you learned.

1983
01:58:56.420 --> 01:58:58.300
So, what did you learn?

1984
01:58:58.920 --> 01:59:02.680
All about volcanoes, earthquakes...

1985
01:59:03.050 --> 01:59:04.090
...plates.

1986
01:59:04.390 --> 01:59:10.180
Convergence and divergence,
movement of the Earth's plates.


1987
01:59:11.440 --> 01:59:13.730
- It was fascinating.
- It interested you?


1988
01:59:13.900 --> 01:59:14.940
That's good.

1989
01:59:15.860 --> 01:59:17.770
Well, in mathematics...

1990
01:59:17.940 --> 01:59:19.440
Trigonometry.

1991
01:59:19.900 --> 01:59:22.110
Pythagoras' theorem,
Thales' theorem.


1992
01:59:22.320 --> 01:59:23.910
I'll stop you there.

1993
01:59:24.070 --> 01:59:26.450
You can't sit there and brag...

1994
01:59:26.620 --> 01:59:29.910
...you learned Pythagoras' theorem.
Recite it for us.


1995
01:59:33.750 --> 01:59:35.330
If in a triangle...

1996
01:59:38.550 --> 01:59:41.590
...two sides are equal to...

1997
01:59:42.090 --> 01:59:43.930
If the square root...

1998
01:59:44.090 --> 01:59:47.140
If the square of two sides
is equal to the square...


1999
01:59:48.060 --> 01:59:50.600
The square of the hypotenuse...

2000
01:59:50.770 --> 01:59:52.640
...then the triangle's a right triangle.

2001
01:59:53.730 --> 01:59:55.310
More or less, yes.

2002
01:59:55.480 --> 01:59:56.810
It's spot on.

2003
01:59:56.980 --> 01:59:58.110
All right.

2004
01:59:58.570 --> 02:00:00.070
I believe you.

2005
02:00:00.480 --> 02:00:03.320
In history,
I learned about triangular trade.


2006
02:00:03.490 --> 02:00:06.820
The fact that ships left Europe...

2007
02:00:06.990 --> 02:00:09.160
...with manufactured goods...

2008
02:00:09.370 --> 02:00:13.410
...that they took to Africa to trade
for men who'd become slaves...


2009
02:00:13.580 --> 02:00:16.290
...that they took to America to work.

2010
02:00:16.460 --> 02:00:19.960
Then they took the money
they made back to Europe.


2011
02:00:20.130 --> 02:00:22.090
That's triangular trade.

2012
02:00:23.010 --> 02:00:24.630
Chemistry.

2013
02:00:24.800 --> 02:00:26.130
What in chemistry?

2014
02:00:27.010 --> 02:00:28.800
Combustion.

2015
02:00:28.970 --> 02:00:30.350
What's that?

2016
02:00:30.510 --> 02:00:34.810
Blending Fehling's solution
and glucose.


2017
02:00:34.980 --> 02:00:36.310
What do you get?

2018
02:00:36.770 --> 02:00:39.440
Heat up the test tube...

2019
02:00:39.610 --> 02:00:41.400
...and it changes color.

2020
02:00:43.190 --> 02:00:44.780
What's the interest?

2021
02:00:44.950 --> 02:00:46.110
The interest?

2022
02:00:46.280 --> 02:00:50.530
I don't know. Why teach it to us
if there's no interest?


2023
02:00:51.410 --> 02:00:53.410
Reproduction.

2024
02:00:55.290 --> 02:00:58.710
What did you learn
about human reproduction?


2025
02:00:59.000 --> 02:01:00.500
Human reproduction.

2026
02:01:00.920 --> 02:01:03.300
Well, the sperm...

2027
02:01:03.670 --> 02:01:05.210
...gets into the ovum...

2028
02:01:05.550 --> 02:01:07.170
...then you wait nine months...

2029
02:01:07.430 --> 02:01:10.970
