How come?

2057
02:02:41.310 --> 02:02:44.230
My big sister had it.

2058
02:02:44.400 --> 02:02:45.820
She does philosophy?

2059
02:02:46.020 --> 02:02:47.270
No, law.

2060
02:02:48.150 --> 02:02:49.650
So, what's it about?

2061
02:02:50.610 --> 02:02:52.990
Well, there's this guy.

2062
02:02:53.160 --> 02:02:54.660
His name's Socrates.

2063
02:02:54.830 --> 02:02:55.910
Socrates.

2064
02:02:56.450 --> 02:03:01.330
He stops people in the street
and he asks them:


2065
02:03:01.540 --> 02:03:05.330
"Are you sure of thinking
what you think?


2066
02:03:05.540 --> 02:03:08.460
Are you sure of doing
what you do?" And so on.


2067
02:03:08.630 --> 02:03:11.760
After that,
people start getting confused.


2068
02:03:11.930 --> 02:03:13.550
They ask questions.

2069
02:03:13.800 --> 02:03:15.340
The guy's too much.

2070
02:03:15.970 --> 02:03:18.180
What does he ask people about?

2071
02:03:18.350 --> 02:03:22.850
Everything. Love, religion, God...

2072
02:03:23.060 --> 02:03:25.270
...people, everything.

2073
02:03:26.270 --> 02:03:28.070
- It's good you read it.
- I know.


2074
02:03:28.690 --> 02:03:30.690
It's not a skank's book.

2075
02:03:36.700 --> 02:03:37.780
Wait a second.

2076
02:03:37.950 --> 02:03:41.000
Before you leave,
here are your self-portraits.


2077
02:03:41.160 --> 02:03:44.370
One by one.
When you have yours, you can go.


2078
02:03:48.460 --> 02:03:51.130
This is kind of you.

2079
02:03:51.380 --> 02:03:52.630
What is it?

2080
02:03:52.800 --> 02:03:55.890
These are the self-portraits
that you wrote...


2081
02:03:56.090 --> 02:03:59.850
...and that we made up
with the class photo and so on.


2082
02:04:02.890 --> 02:04:04.100
You don't have one?

2083
02:04:06.980 --> 02:04:08.900
Why did you put this here?

2084
02:04:09.110 --> 02:04:11.610
- You look good in it.
- Cut it out.


2085
02:04:11.860 --> 02:04:13.860
You're like a leader.

2086
02:04:19.160 --> 02:04:21.660
- Have a good vacation.
- You too.


2087
02:04:28.420 --> 02:04:29.500
Sir?

2088
02:04:32.130 --> 02:04:33.260
What is it?

2089
02:04:34.340 --> 02:04:36.260
I didn't learn anything.

2090
02:04:38.430 --> 02:04:40.640
What? That doesn't mean anything.

2091
02:04:42.270 --> 02:04:44.350
Earlier, all the others...

2092
02:04:44.520 --> 02:04:47.730
...said they'd learned something.

2093
02:04:49.270 --> 02:04:51.650
Compared to them, 
I learned nothing.

2094
02:04:55.150 --> 02:04:59.530
You learned as much as them.
They had to think hard too.


2095
02:04:59.700 --> 02:05:01.240
It's not easy...

2096
02:05:01.410 --> 02:05:04.700
...to remember what you learned.

2097
02:05:05.160 --> 02:05:06.660
But I don't understand.

2098
02:05:07.790 --> 02:05:08.960
What do you mean?

2099
02:05:09.670 --> 02:05:11.750
I don't understand what we do.

2100
02:05:12.380 --> 02:05:13.420
In French?

2101
02:05:14.670 --> 02:05:15.800
In everything.

2102
02:05:17.680 --> 02:05:21.970
You can't say you don't understand
anything in any subject.


2103
02:05:22.760 --> 02:05:24.770
That's not true.

2104
02:05:27.560 --> 02:05:30.400
I don't want to go
to vocational school.


2105
02:05:31.400 --> 02:05:33.820
There's no question of that yet.

2106
02:05:34.730 --> 02:05:36.990
You're moving on to the next year.

2107
02:05:37.570 --> 02:05:41.820
You'll have plenty of time
to think about your future.


2108
02:05:41.990 --> 02:05:45.290
Vocational school
isn't an absolute certainty.


2109
02:05:45.450 --> 02:05:48.080
It all depends
on how you do next year.


2110
02:05:49.790 --> 02:05:51.080
But I don't want to.